<bug>
    <id>319364</id>
    <title>Holding CTRL While Highlighting causes problmes</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.8) Gecko/20051111 Firefox/1.5
Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.8) Gecko/20051111 Firefox/1.5</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">If you hold down CTRL and try and highlight a paragraph from text.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">Then move to left, it does a strange highlight.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">Even worse, if you let up on the CTRL there is no way of clicking that will bring it back to normal highlighting mode.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">This problem could also be related to some sites not copying URLs correctly if they are right next to a table edge, like Amazon's wish list.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Reproducible: Always</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.2">1 Go to http://www.cnn.com/2005/TRAVEL/12/06/virgin.space/index.html</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.3">2 Hold down CTRL</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.4">3 Highlight a paragraph and hold down mouse</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.5">4 move mose too far to left until it does strange highlight (maybe table?)</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.6">5 let go of CTRL</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.7">6 you will be unable to normally select anything anymore</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
